    <b>Rancorous Reptiles</b></font><br>
    <font class=tiny><b>Date:</b> Tuesday, February 26 @ 17:31:22 EST<br><b>Topic:</b> Everquest</font><br><br>
    </center>
    <font class="content">
    After a day beguiling befuddlement by Verant with their ineptitude in flawless patching, we spent what was left of the evening the Ssraezha Temple, biding ado to the Glyph Covered Serpent, Exiled Serpent, our (and Server-First™) attempt on the Cursed (who’s never been killed anywhere), and ended the evening with Xerkizh the Creator.  <br><br>

<img src="http://www.lotuscult.com/~quixotim/otherpics/glcsbehind.jpg">
<img src="http://www.lotuscult.com/~quixotim/otherpics/gcs022502.jpg"><br><br>
<img src="http://www.lotuscult.com/~quixotim/otherpics/exiledduelwield.jpg">
<img src="http://www.lotuscult.com/~quixotim/otherpics/exiled022502.jpg"><br><br>
<img src="http://www.lotuscult.com/~quixotim/otherpics/creatorsideview.jpg">
<img src="http://www.lotuscult.com/~quixotim/otherpics/creator022502.jpg"><br><br>


It appears the recent foible with the Glyph Covered Serpent spawn was defoiblized with the most recent patch.  He quickly arrived and was rather expeditiously disposed.  He departed with the all-to-common <b><a href="http://www.lotuscult.com/~quixotim/loot/rancorousskullofszaldrezh.jpg">Rancorous Skull of Szaldrezh</a></b>, awarded to Xaxilis.   Shortly thereafter, we faced and bested the Exiled.  I’m not sure who determined the Exiled should come after the Glyphed, thereby suggested greater difficult.  If this was the case, it was blunderous indeed.   <b><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=2457">Obfob</a></b> took our first ever obtained Elphorn’s Cleaver and <b><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=2171">Quixotim</a></b> looted the next Skull so it wouldn’t rot.  Afterwards, we engaged The Cursed.  I have no pictures because I help pull him and he tore through my 6200 HPs like it was butter.  It was humbling to stay alive as long as we did, even landing slow and most debuffs on him.  Now, we just need about 45 more manaburn wizards and all will be good.  Finally, we ended the evening with Xirkizh, who bequeathed unto us two new items, both of splendid worth.  Iguan departed with the headband and <b><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=1548">Ebobulous</a></b> departed with the paladin staff.  
<br><br>

